			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did the copper medal of war quest tonight with myself (58 Beastlord), and my two friends (63 enchanter and 63 shaman).  It was too easy.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
You don't need the acrylia sphere any more; just hail Scout Husman, and tell him you are here to help.  When you're ready to proceed, tell him, "I am ready."
<br />

<br />
Within 1 minute he'll start running; follow him to the camp north of the vah shir outpost.  He'll stop and tell you to clear the outpost, and be careful not to fall under the spells of the shamen in the camp.   He'll wait until you say, "I am ready to begin" then he wishes you luck, and leaves.
<br />

<br />
We cleared the camp easily, perhaps 30 grimlings or so, all green to me.  There are four spiritcallers that stand around the fire, that you cannot target until all others are dead.  When you've killed everything you're supposed to, then you can target and kill the spiritcallers.   (Green to me also).  The Copper Medal of War will drop from one of these spiritcallers.  After the spiritcallers are dead, Soul Echo will spawn.  (Head honcho, I guess)  He's a shammie too, but went down real easy.  He dropped this:  <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=11837url" target="_blank" class="postlink">Small Twisted Stave</a><br />_________________<br /><div align="center"> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
[url=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=419959][img]</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
