				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, my friend and I camped in Grimling for FIVE days, for a minimum of 5 hours a day, up to 12 hours on one, killing bandits and couriers and had ONE medal drop.  He was a level higher than me and had been there a bit longer, so he got it.  That was three days in.  He stuck with me through my camp and we never got another drop off the couriers, after 35ish kills.  Ultra-rare drop off a rare mob is NOT cool.  Finally, I stayed up way late the 5th night, and logged on my 62 druid and my roommate's 65 rogue and proceeded to lay waste to the camps intending to log my BL on to loot.  About 6am pst, the camp suddenly became populated with Grimlings, the war FINALLY freaking reset.  So I did two wars (camp 2 didn't drop, but camp 5 did) with the help of a 65 wiz who wanted to see how to do the wars for his BL.  Then did two more for him, as the first war for him didn't drop it, either.
<br />

<br />
My advice?  Check back periodically for the war.  Bandits can suck it.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=233897" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Asharia Oakenheart</span></a>
